cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the application of deep learning-based autoencoders in communication systems, specifically for beyond-5G systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also proposes a novel online adaptive deep learning algorithm, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep learning in communication systems also involves the optimization of neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The proposed algorithm is designed to improve the robustness of the autoencoder under interference channels, which involves control and system identification, falling under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper also involves simulations and performance evaluation, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
